---
// FAQ Section Component
---

<section
    id="faq"
    class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 border-t border-[#2A2F3A]"
>
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <div
            class="text-cyan-400 text-sm font-bold tracking-widest uppercase mb-3"
        >
            Common Questions
        </div>
        <h2
            class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tighter text-gray-100"
        >
            Frequently Asked Questions.
        </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
        <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
        <div
            class="border border-[#2A2F3A] bg-[#0A0D12] rounded-xl overflow-hidden"
        >
            <button
                class="faq-btn w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left hover:bg-[#0F131A] transition"
                aria-expanded="false"
            >
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-200 pr-8"
                    >What do I get for $5,000?</span
                >
                <i
                    data-lucide="chevron-down"
                    class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 shrink-0 transition-transform"
                ></i>
            </button>
            <div
                class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
                <p class="mb-3">
                    You get a fully functional, production-ready MVP with:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mb-3 text-gray-400">
                    <li>1-2 Core features (fully polished)</li>
                    <li>Secure authentication (Session-based/OAuth)</li>
                    <li>Database design with proper indexing</li>
                    <li>API documentation (OpenAPI/Swagger)</li>
                    <li>Security: SQL injection prevention, XSS protection</li>
                    <li>Deployment with CI/CD pipeline</li>
                    <li>14-day bug fix warranty</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    <strong class="text-emerald-400"
                        >Yes, it's production-ready.</strong
                    > Your MVP will be live on secure servers with SSL, ready to onboard
                    paying customers from day one. Everything needed to start acquiring
                    users and validating your idea, built with 11+ years of engineering
                    expertise.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
        <div
            class="border border-[#2A2F3A] bg-[#0A0D12] rounded-xl overflow-hidden"
        >
            <button
                class="faq-btn w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left hover:bg-[#0F131A] transition"
                aria-expanded="false"
            >
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-200 pr-8"
                    >Do I own the code and IP?</span
                >
                <i
                    data-lucide="chevron-down"
                    class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 shrink-0 transition-transform"
                ></i>
            </button>
            <div
                class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
                <p>
                    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Yes, 100%.</strong> Unlike agencies
                    that retain partial ownership or charge licensing fees, you receive
                    complete IP handover. All code, designs, and documentation belong
                    to you. You can hire another developer tomorrow without any legal
                    complications.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
        <div
            class="border border-[#2A2F3A] bg-[#0A0D12] rounded-xl overflow-hidden"
        >
            <button
                class="faq-btn w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left hover:bg-[#0F131A] transition"
                aria-expanded="false"
            >
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-200 pr-8"
                    >What about ongoing support after launch?</span
                >
                <i
                    data-lucide="chevron-down"
                    class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 shrink-0 transition-transform"
                ></i>
            </button>
            <div
                class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
                <p>
                    I offer optional ongoing support retainers at <strong
                        class="text-gray-300">$4,000/month</strong
                    > for bug fixes, feature additions, and maintenance. This includes:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2 text-gray-400">
                    <li>Priority bug fixes (24-48h response)</li>
                    <li>Up to 15 hours feature development</li>
                    <li>Server monitoring & uptime alerts</li>
                    <li>Dependency updates & security patches</li>
                    <li>Dedicated Slack/Email channel</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    You're never locked in—you can hire anyone else since you
                    own the code.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
        <div
            class="border border-[#2A2F3A] bg-[#0A0D12] rounded-xl overflow-hidden"
        >
            <button
                class="faq-btn w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left hover:bg-[#0F131A] transition"
                aria-expanded="false"
            >
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-200 pr-8"
                    >What technologies do you use?</span
                >
                <i
                    data-lucide="chevron-down"
                    class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 shrink-0 transition-transform"
                ></i>
            </button>
            <div
                class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
                <p>I tailor the stack to your needs, but typically use:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mb-3 text-gray-400">
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300">Frontend:</strong> Svelte/React
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300">Backend:</strong> Go/Bun
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300">Database:</strong> PostgreSQL/SQLite
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300">Deploy:</strong> VPS / Cloud
                        Server (not serverless)
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    <strong class="text-emerald-400"
                        >Why VPS, not Vercel/serverless?</strong
                    > Serverless looks cheap until you get traffic. Then you get hit
                    with unpredictable bills. I use traditional VPS hosting with <strong
                        class="text-gray-300">fixed monthly costs</strong
                    > ($5-20/month) so you can scale without surprise charges. Plus:
                    no vendor lock-in, full control, and easier to migrate.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-2">
                    Stripe for payments and authentication included from day
                    one. All code is production-grade with proper security,
                    testing, and documentation.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
        <div
            class="border border-[#2A2F3A] bg-[#0A0D12] rounded-xl overflow-hidden"
        >
            <button
                class="faq-btn w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left hover:bg-[#0F131A] transition"
                aria-expanded="false"
            >
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-200 pr-8"
                    >How do we communicate during the project?</span
                >
                <i
                    data-lucide="chevron-down"
                    class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 shrink-0 transition-transform"
                ></i>
            </button>
            <div
                class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
                <p>
                    We start with <strong class="text-gray-300"
                        >one kickoff call</strong
                    > to align on scope and architecture. After that, communication
                    is asynchronous via Slack, Email, or Notion. This allows me to
                    focus on writing code instead of sitting in meetings. You'll receive
                    regular progress updates without the friction of scheduled calls.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
        <div
            class="border border-[#2A2F3A] bg-[#0A0D12] rounded-xl overflow-hidden"
        >
            <button
                class="faq-btn w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left hover:bg-[#0F131A] transition"
                aria-expanded="false"
            >
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-200 pr-8"
                    >How long does it take?</span
                >
                <i
                    data-lucide="chevron-down"
                    class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 shrink-0 transition-transform"
                ></i>
            </button>
            <div
                class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
                <p>Timeline depends on the tier:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2 text-gray-400">
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300">Starter ($5,000):</strong> 1-2
                        weeks
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300">Growth ($8,000):</strong> 2-3
                        weeks
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300">Scale ($12,000):</strong> 3-4
                        weeks
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    During our kickoff call, we'll <strong class="text-gray-300"
                        >ruthlessly prioritize features</strong
                    > and lock the scope. This fixed-scope approach is why I can guarantee
                    on-time delivery. Non-essential features can be added post-launch.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 7 -->
        <div
            class="border border-[#2A2F3A] bg-[#0A0D12] rounded-xl overflow-hidden"
        >
            <button
                class="faq-btn w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left hover:bg-[#0F131A] transition"
                aria-expanded="false"
            >
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-200 pr-8"
                    >What happens if the project takes longer than 4 weeks?</span
                >
                <i
                    data-lucide="chevron-down"
                    class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 shrink-0 transition-transform"
                ></i>
            </button>
            <div
                class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
                <p>
                    <strong class="text-emerald-400"
                        >This is extremely rare.</strong
                    > In 11+ years of building software, I've delivered every project
                    on time. Here's how we ensure it:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2 text-gray-400">
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300"
                            >Fixed scope upfront:</strong
                        > Before we start, we document every feature in detail. No
                        vague requirements—everything is crystal clear
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300"
                            >No mid-project changes:</strong
                        > Once we begin, the scope is locked. This prevents "scope
                        creep" that kills timelines
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300"
                            >Minor changes only:</strong
                        > Small adjustments (copy, colors, minor UI tweaks) are fine.
                        Major feature additions get postponed to post-launch
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300">Buffer built-in:</strong> Timeline
                        estimates already include contingency for unexpected challenges
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300"
                            >Weekly progress updates:</strong
                        > You'll know immediately if anything threatens the timeline—no
                        surprises
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    <strong class="text-cyan-400"
                        >If delays happen (rare):</strong
                    > I'll communicate early, explain the blocker, and offer options—whether
                    it's launching with core features first or adjusting scope. You're
                    never left in the dark.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    <strong class="text-gray-300">Bottom line:</strong> Clear scope
                    + disciplined execution = on-time delivery. Every time.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 8 -->
        <div
            class="border border-[#2A2F3A] bg-[#0A0D12] rounded-xl overflow-hidden"
        >
            <button
                class="faq-btn w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left hover:bg-[#0F131A] transition"
                aria-expanded="false"
            >
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-200 pr-8"
                    >Do you use AI for coding?</span
                >
                <i
                    data-lucide="chevron-down"
                    class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 shrink-0 transition-transform"
                ></i>
            </button>
            <div
                class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
                <p>
                    Yes, I use modern AI tools to accelerate development—but
                    with <strong class="text-gray-300"
                        >11+ years of engineering expertise</strong
                    > guiding every decision. The difference:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2 text-gray-400">
                    <li>Security-first architecture (not copy-paste code)</li>
                    <li>Proper testing and error handling</li>
                    <li>Scalable design patterns</li>
                    <li>Production-ready documentation</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    AI gives me velocity. Experience gives you reliability.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 9 -->
        <div
            class="border border-[#2A2F3A] bg-[#0A0D12] rounded-xl overflow-hidden"
        >
            <button
                class="faq-btn w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left hover:bg-[#0F131A] transition"
                aria-expanded="false"
            >
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-200 pr-8"
                    >Will the design look professional or just functional?</span
                >
                <i
                    data-lucide="chevron-down"
                    class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 shrink-0 transition-transform"
                ></i>
            </button>
            <div
                class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
                <p>
                    <strong class="text-emerald-400"
                        >Professional. Always.</strong
                    > I'm not just a developer who ships code—I have strong design
                    taste and attention to detail. You can see the quality in my portfolio:
                    Laju.dev, Slugpost.com, Antre.in, KlikAja.app and more.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-3">Here's my process:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2 text-gray-400">
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300"
                            >Pre-kickoff visual design:</strong
                        > Before we start building, I'll present the scope document
                        with visual mockups/design system so you can see exactly how
                        your app will look
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300">Clean, modern UI:</strong> I
                        use proven design patterns—crisp typography, proper spacing,
                        consistent colors, and intuitive UX
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong class="text-gray-300"
                            >Portfolio-grade output:</strong
                        > Every project I ship is something I'm proud to showcase.
                        Your MVP will look like a funded startup, not a side project
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    <strong class="text-cyan-400"
                        >Not satisfied with the initial design?</strong
                    > You can cancel before we start development. No hard feelings.
                    I'd rather walk away than build something we're both unhappy with.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    <strong class="text-gray-300">Bottom line:</strong> Your product
                    will look polished enough to impress investors and early users
                    from day one.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 10 -->
        <div
            class="border border-[#2A2F3A] bg-[#0A0D12] rounded-xl overflow-hidden"
        >
            <button
                class="faq-btn w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left hover:bg-[#0F131A] transition"
                aria-expanded="false"
            >
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-200 pr-8"
                    >Can this scale to 100,000+ users?</span
                >
                <i
                    data-lucide="chevron-down"
                    class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 shrink-0 transition-transform"
                ></i>
            </button>
            <div
                class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
                <p>
                    <strong class="text-emerald-400">Yes. Proven.</strong> My SQLite
                    + Go architecture is benchmarked at <strong
                        class="text-gray-300"
                        >100,000+ requests per second</strong
                    > on a single $200/month VPS with sub-millisecond latency.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    For context: 100k RPS can handle ~8.6 billion requests per
                    day. Most startups never reach this scale. If you do hit
                    massive traffic, the architecture supports horizontal
                    scaling with read replicas and sharding.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    <strong class="text-cyan-400"
                        >Read the technical breakdown:</strong
                    >
                    <a
                        href="https://laju.dev/blog/sqlite-blueprint-en/"
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noopener noreferrer"
                        class="underline hover:text-cyan-300"
                        >laju.dev/blog/sqlite-blueprint</a
                    >
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Item 11 -->
        <div
            class="border border-[#2A2F3A] bg-[#0A0D12] rounded-xl overflow-hidden"
        >
            <button
                class="faq-btn w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left hover:bg-[#0F131A] transition"
                aria-expanded="false"
            >
                <span class="font-bold text-gray-200 pr-8"
                    >What's the payment structure?</span
                >
                <i
                    data-lucide="chevron-down"
                    class="w-5 h-5 text-cyan-400 shrink-0 transition-transform"
                ></i>
            </button>
            <div
                class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6 text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
            >
                <p>
                    We use <strong class="text-cyan-400">Escrow.com</strong> to guarantee
                    100% financial security. Here's how it works:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2 text-gray-400">
                    <li>
                        You deposit the project funds into a secure third-party
                        escrow account
                    </li>
                    <li>I build your MVP in 2-4 weeks</li>
                    <li>
                        The funds are only released to me <strong
                            class="text-gray-300">AFTER</strong
                        > you approve the final product
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        You receive the full source code and complete IP
                        ownership
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-3">
                    <strong class="text-emerald-400">Zero upfront risk.</strong> Your
                    money stays protected until you're satisfied with the delivered
                    MVP.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<script>
    // FAQ accordion functionality
    document.querySelectorAll(".faq-btn").forEach((button) => {
        button.addEventListener("click", () => {
            const content = button.nextElementSibling as HTMLElement;
            const icon = button.querySelector("i");
            const isExpanded = button.getAttribute("aria-expanded") === "true";

            // Toggle current item
            button.setAttribute("aria-expanded", String(!isExpanded));
            content.classList.toggle("hidden");
            icon?.classList.toggle("rotate-180", !isExpanded);
        });
    });
</script>
